🔊 SOMOS A TODAH MUSIC
A palavra TODAH vem da mesma raiz que YADAH, significa “mãos estendidas”.
Então a expressão TODAH, que também é usada como agradecimento (OBRIGADO) traz em sua raiz uma relação com “estender as mãos”. 
Estar agradecido é estender as mãos aos céus e reconhecer tudo o que Deus tem feito em nossas vidas.

Mas eu tenho uma palavra 
 
Vai ter continuidade

não ficará pela metade 
A obra não termina aqui

Você tem autoridade

Então reage

Escolhido não pode escolher

Te escolheu pra nascer

Title: IS THIS THE HOTTEST NEW ROCKSTAR OF 2023?! #music #emo #punkrock #hardrock #rocksong #rock #rockstar
Sabrina Carpenter: Tiny Desk Concert
Description:
Ashley Pointer | December 20, 2024
When I greeted Sabrina Carpenter at NPR HQ for her Tiny Desk debut, her charm was immediately disarming. Bubbling with excitement, she extended her hand, introduced herself and complimented my outfit with genuine warmth. You’d think this was one of her first “big time” gigs, not a regular performance for a pop veteran, having sold out arenas across the country touring her now six time Grammy-nominated sixth album, Short n’ Sweet. That humility made me love her even more. 

But Carpenter delivers far more than just charm in this performance. Backed by her band, complimented with pedal steel and a string quartet, she reimagines her biggest hits from Short n’ Sweet, while sharing the stories in between songs of how these tracks came to life. Opening with “Taste,” strings serve up some playful pizzicato, before Carpenter and her band move into a lush, soulful version “Bed Chem.” Then everyone swaps their electric instruments for acoustic to perform “Please Please Please” and “Slim Pickins.” Finally, Carpenter closes with the viral favorite “Juno,” cheekily asking the audience, “Have you ever tried this one?” before sweeping her rear end across the windchimes, earning a laugh from the room. 

“When I first started [writing songs] it was kinda in a room like this — a room with very dry walls and there’s no reverb,” Carpenter reflects at the top of her performance. “But there’s something so real and special.” That authenticity set the tone for a memorable session with one of 2024’s biggest breakout superstars.

Title: LEIKA GARUDITA - SAHABAT (OFFICIAL MUSIC VIDEO)
Description:
Dengan nada yang tulus dan lirik yang sederhana namun menyentuh, lagu "Sahabat" ciptaan Leika Garudita menyuarakan indahnya persahabatan. Lagu ini merupakan curahan hati Leika yang merasakan hangatnya persahabatan. Leika berharap, persahabatan ini akan menjadi sebuah perjalanan yang terus ada hingga mereka dewasa. Lirik dan nada dasar lagu ini diciptakan oleh Leika dengan beberapa bantuan dari sang Ayah (Ilman Hidayat), Bunda (Diena Fitri), Om Saka, dan Om Wisnu dalam pengolahannya. Leika berharap lagu ini tidak hanya menjadi pengingat #sahabat untuk teman seusianya saja, namun juga orang dewasa yang merindukan kehadiran #sahabat.

PROFILE
[ 作詞・作曲・編曲・歌唱：私 ] 新世代クリエイター、紫 今（ムラサキイマ）

ハスキー、パワフル、繊細な歌声、かつホイッスルボイスを含む、ハイトーンボイスまで使い分ける抜群の歌唱力を持ち、作詞、作曲、編曲をすべて自ら行う22歳のクリエイター。

2023年、SNSで話題となった楽曲「ゴールデンタイム」をもって、配信でのリリースを開始。
その後リリースしたEP「Gallery」に収録の「凡人様」は、TikTok～YouTube～配信と多岐にわたってバイラル。12月には「Not Queen」がFM802ヘビーローテーションに選出された。

2024年4月リリースの「魔性の女A」は日本国内のみならず、アジア圏も巻き込んで、バイラルし続けている。8～9月にかけて開催の初ワンマンライブ「Mulasaki Ima LIVE 2024 "Episode 0"」は東阪ともにソールドアウト。年末には関東では初のフェス出演として、「COUNTDOWN JAPAN 24/25」への出演がアナウンスされている。

2025年3月12日(水)、ファーストフルアルバム「eMulsion」をリリース。3～4月には東名阪でのワンマンツアー「Mulasaki Ima LIVE 2025 eMulsion」を開催。

A tranquil lake reflects the silvery moonlight of the snowy winter night, while snowflakes gently drift down, blanketing the landscape. Title: Gracie Abrams - I Love You, I'm Sorry

Gracie Abrams - I Love You, I'm Sorry

» Apoyo Gracie Abrams:



(Lyrics):
[Verse 1]
Two Augusts ago
I told the truth, oh, but you didn't like it, you went home
You're in your Benz, I'm by the gate
Now you go alone
Charm all the people you train for, you mean well but aim low
And I'll make it known like I'm getting paid

[Chorus]

I love you, I'm sorry

Two summers from now
We'll have been talking, but not all that often, we're cool now
I'll be on a boat, you're on a plane going somewhere, same
And I'll have a drink
Wistfully lean out my window and watch the sun set on the lake
I might not feel real, but it's okay, mm

[Chorus]
'Cause that's just the way life goes
I push my luck, it shows
Thankful you don't send someone to kill me
I love you, I'm sorry

[Bridge]
You were the best but you were the worst
As sick as it sounds, I loved you first
I was a dick, it is what it is
A habit to kick, the age-old curse
I tend to laugh whenever I'm sad
I stare at the crash, it actually works
Making amends, this shit never ends
I'm wrong again, wrong again

The way life goes
Joyriding down our road
Lay on the horn to prove that it haunts me
(I'm wrong again, wrong again)
I love you, I'm sorry
The way life goes
(You were the best but you were the worst)

I wanna speak in code

(A habit to kick, the age-old curse)
Hope that I don't, won't make it about me

(I stare at the crash, it actually works)
I love you, I'm sorry

Title: Believer Music Video! Sung by the Fun Squad (Imagine Dragons Cover)
Description:
Believer Music Video! Sung by the Fun Squad (Imagine Dragons Cover) Fun Squad Family and the @ImagineDragons charity, TRF @trfdotorg, team up to share the fight against pediatric cancer through the eyes of a survivor.  The story is uniquely told through music video, as the Fun Squad Family musician teens, Jack, Jazzy and Kade Skye, sing a cover of the Imagine Dragons’ song, Believer in a captivating depiction of real-life courage and bravery, Averi of @OurFantasticFive .

OUR GOAL: Help us raise $100K for kids with cancer and hit 5M views of AWARENESS for TRF! What can you do? SHARE THE VIDEO and DONATE! Title: Doechii: Tiny Desk Concert
Description:
Ashley Pointer | December 6, 2024
Doechii, known as the "Swamp Princess," arrived at NPR HQ radiating confidence. She moved with purpose, knowing exactly what she wanted and how to achieve it. Her declarative statement, "I'm everything," from "BOOM BAP" off her Grammy-nominated mixtape, ALLIGATOR BITES NEVER HEAL, was on full display in her Tiny Desk debut.

Backed by a full band, horns and two background singers, Doechii's performance was a masterclass in creativity. Sporting vintage academia looks, complete with matching cornrows and beads, Doechii delivers a freshly rearranged medley of cuts from ALLIGATOR BITES NEVER HEAL, tailored specifically for Tiny Desk. While hip-hop remained at the core, she truly gave us everything: a jazz arrangement of "BOOM BAP," heavy rock vibes on "CATFISH" and a Southern praise break outro on "NISSAN ALTIMA."

She closed her set with "Black Girl Memoir" from her debut album, Oh The Places You'll Go. Before performing, she shared, "I wrote this song specifically for Black women. As a dark-skinned woman, there's a very unique experience I'm trying to internalize … This is dedicated to all the beautiful Black women in the room." While her star has been steadily on the rise since her debut, 2024 is shaping up to be the year Doechii cements herself as a household name.

Title: (NO MID-ROLL ADS) Winter Solstice | Inspired by ACOTAR Relaxing Music & Ambience for Fantasy Reading
Description:
The atmosphere in the townhouse in Velaris during the Winter Solstice is one of tranquil beauty, wrapped in the quiet embrace of snowfall and the warmth of hearth and home. The room is softly lit by the golden glow of the fireplace, its flickering flames casting delicate shadows on the richly paneled walls. The fire crackles and pops, the sound grounding the cozy interior with a soothing, rhythmic heartbeat.

Beyond the arched Victorian windows, snow falls steadily in thick, lazy flakes, blanketing the cobblestone streets of Velaris. The storm hums in the background, a low, muffled howl that’s both distant and comforting, like a protective cocoon around the home. The town’s soft glow reflects off the snow, sending a faint silver-blue light into the room, contrasting beautifully with the warm orange of the fire.

The room itself is intimate yet grand in its details. A plush velvet sofa sits before the fireplace, piled high with soft throws and cushions, inviting anyone to sink into its comfort. Nearby, an ornate armchair cradles an open book, abandoned in favor of watching the snow swirl outside. On a side table, steaming mugs of mulled wine and small plates of spiced biscuits sit waiting, their rich scents mingling with the earthy smell of the burning wood.

The air is imbued with the gentle strains of peaceful piano music, the delicate notes weaving through the room like a second snowfall—soft, calming, and introspective. Each note feels like a memory, echoing the quiet joy of the Winter Solstice and the bonds of the Inner Circle. The music blends seamlessly with the other sounds: the crackle of the fire, the hushed roar of the storm, and the occasional creak of the house as it settles into the night.

This space feels like a haven, a pause in time where the worries of the world fade into the background. It’s a moment of reflection, companionship, and serenity, perfectly suited to the peaceful magic of Velaris and the intimacy of the Winter Solstice.

Title: LOVE Is The Answer! Emotional Story and Music Video, by Sarah Skye
Description:
Love is the Answer.  When you are mistreated, how do you choose to respond?  Most of us respond out of fear or hurt, but we can choose to respond with kindness and love.  This song was written and sung by Sarah Skye, Fun Squad Momma, to inspire others to reach with love and change the world one person at a time.  We can't ever see why people behave the way they do, but we can choose to be our best selves by showing love.  One of my favorite quotes is, "In the quiet heart is hidden, sorrow that they eye can't see."  Often loved ones behave poorly because they've been hurt themselves.  Let's all respond with love.  It is the answer for our generation. #love #loveistheanswer #sarahskye #funsquadmusic
